dct_description_sm: Relief shown by 2.5 meter contour intervals and spot heights. Map locates builidings occupied by the Japanese, non-Allied Forces, Allied forces, military roads. Shows precint, sub-precint, and ward administrative boundaries Includes index to glossary, coverage diagram, and index to boundaries. "Place names transcribed according to the Modified Hepburn (Romaji) System." "Compiled in 1948 from aerial photographs flown by the US Air Force in 1945 and 1947. Map detailed intensified by field survey with the exception of Imperial Palace ground." "Repro. by the 64th Engr. Base Topo BN."
dct_publisher_sm: [Washington, D.C.] : United States Far East Command, 1948.
